Introduction

Kim Gaeul is a South Korean dancer, rapper, and singer-songwriter under Starship Entertainment. She is best known as the lead rapper and sub vocalist of the girl group IVE.

Gaeul's passion for dancing led her to join numerous competitions. Though initially her parents disapproved of a casting agent's offer, they later agreed to support her talent if she got scouted again. During another competition, she was discovered by Starship Entertainment. After passing the audition, she became an official trainee and eventually debuted as a member of IVE.

On November 12, 2021, Gaeul was revealed as the fourth member of IVE. The group officially debuted on December 1, 2021, with their single album "ELEVEN".
